						<summary>

						<p>Rock called Sanyāsiguṇḍu on the Vāmi-koṇḍa halli.</p>						

						<p>This undated archaic Telugu epigraph may be assigned to the 7th century, on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>It states that the excellent teacher Vṛishabha who was a cloud to the crops, money to the righteous <hi rend="italic">(bhavyas)</hi> and an unshakable rock to his opponents, in discourse, lived on this hill.</p>						

						</summary>
